<HL>
   Technology Brief -- Lotus Development Corp.:
   Product for Apple Computer
   Will Create Marketing Lists
</HL>
<DATE>
04/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B3
</SO>
<CO>
   LOTS AAPL
</CO>
<IN>
SOFTWARE (SOF)
</IN>
<LP>
   Lotus Development Corp. said it will make a new product
for Apple Computer Inc.'s Macintosh personal computers that
combines compact-disk, read-only memory data bases on U.S.
businesses and households with software for creating
marketing lists.
   Available in the third quarter of 1990, Lotus MarketPlace,
priced at $695, will be distributed through computer software
retailers.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Lotus, based in Cambridge, Mass., and Apple, in Cupertino,
Calif., also announced an agreement under which the companies
will market the product through a number of cooperative
programs during the year.
</TEXT>
